<h2>Page layouts</h2>
<p>
    COMPASS uses consistent page layouts to provide a familiar experience across all features.
</p>

<h3>Standard page structure</h3>
<div class="component-example">
    <div class="component-example-title">Example structure</div>
    <pre><code>&lt;div class="content-wrapper"&gt;
    &lt;div class="content-header"&gt;
        &lt;!-- Breadcrumbs --&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;section class="content" id="main-content"&gt;
        &lt;div class="container-fluid"&gt;
            &lt;!-- Page content --&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/section&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
</div>

<h3>Container widths</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Full width</strong> - Use <code>container-fluid</code> for full-width layouts</li>
    <li><strong>Content area</strong> - Main content uses full width with appropriate padding</li>
    <li><strong>Cards</strong> - Use Bootstrap grid system for responsive layouts</li>
</ul>

<h2>Links</h2>
<p>
    Links should be clearly identifiable and follow consistent styling.
</p>

<h3>Link styles</h3>
<div class="component-example">
    <div class="component-example-title">Example</div>
    <p>
        This is a <a href="#">standard link</a> in body text.
    </p>
    <p>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Primary button link</a>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-secondary">Secondary button link</a>
    </p>
</div>

<h3>Link guidelines</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Links use the primary blue colour (#1d70b8)</li>
    <li>Links should be underlined in body text</li>
    <li>Link text should be descriptive (avoid "click here")</li>
    <li>External links should open in a new tab with appropriate ARIA labels</li>
    <li>Visited links use a darker shade (#003078)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Dates</h2>
<p>
    Dates should be formatted consistently throughout COMPASS.
</p>

<h3>Date formats</h3>
<div class="component-example">
    <div class="component-example-title">Example</div>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Full date:</strong> 15 January 2025</li>
        <li><strong>Short date:</strong> 15/01/2025</li>
        <li><strong>Month and year:</strong> January 2025</li>
        <li><strong>Relative:</strong> 2 days ago, last week</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<h3>Date formatting guidelines</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Use full date format (15 January 2025) for clarity in most contexts</li>
    <li>Use short date format (15/01/2025) only in tables or compact spaces</li>
    <li>Use relative dates (2 days ago) for recent activity</li>
    <li>Always include the year for dates more than 6 months old</li>
    <li>Use consistent date formatting within the same page or feature</li>
</ul>

<h2>Names</h2>
<p>
    Person names should be displayed consistently and respectfully.
</p>

<h3>Name formats</h3>
<div class="component-example">
    <div class="component-example-title">Example</div>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Full name:</strong> John Smith</li>
        <li><strong>With title:</strong> Dr. Jane Doe</li>
        <li><strong>Initials:</strong> J. Smith (when space is limited)</li>
        <li><strong>Last name first:</strong> Smith, John (in lists or tables)</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<h3>Name display guidelines</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Use full names (First Last) in most contexts</li>
    <li>Respect user preferences for name display</li>
    <li>In tables, use consistent format (either "First Last" or "Last, First")</li>
    <li>Include titles or roles when relevant (e.g., "Dr. Jane Doe")</li>
    <li>Use initials only when space is very limited</li>
</ul>

<h2>Products</h2>
<p>
    Product names and information should be displayed consistently.
</p>

<h3>Product display formats</h3>
<div class="component-example">
    <div class="component-example-title">Example</div>
    <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="dfe-adminui-card__body">
            <h4 class="card-title">Product Name</h4>
            <p class="card-text">
                <strong>Product ID:</strong> PROD-12345<br>
                <strong>Status:</strong> <span class="dfe-adminui-badge dfe-adminui-badge--success">Active</span><br>
                <strong>Owner:</strong> John Smith
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<h3>Product formatting guidelines</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Product names should be in sentence case</li>
    <li>Use consistent product ID format (e.g., PROD-12345)</li>
    <li>Display product status using badges</li>
    <li>Include relevant metadata (owner, dates, status) consistently</li>
    <li>Use cards or containers to group product information</li>
</ul>
